The paper discusses the use of deep learning approaches for solving inverse problems in signal and image processing, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a new generalization bound and regularization strategies, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper presents numerical results on various datasets, which is relevant to the sub-category of scientific computing (cs.SI).
